{"lemma":"خَبٌّ","slug":"خَبٌّ","root":"خ.ب.ب","root_slug":"خ-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":8},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9827"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to subside, to sink in"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to alight and abode in a depressed tract or ground, in order that one’s place might not be known (like e. g. to avoid claims upon one’s hospitability)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become deceitful"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to trot, to gallop easily"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to waw, to undulate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deception, fraud, verbal noun of خَبَّ (ḵabba) (form I)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"deceiver, cheater","examples":[{"text":"لَا يَدْخُلُ الْجَنَّةَ خِبٌّ وَلَا مَنَّانٌ وَلَا بَخِيلٌ","english":"The cheater, the laudicenus and the miser don’t enter paradise."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"waw, wave"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9827","headword_ar":"خَبٌّ","root":"xb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, A, L, Msb, K) [said in the Msb to be originally an inf. n.] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~N","text_ar":"خِبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K) [originally an inf. n. accord. to most authorities] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xub~N","text_ar":"خُبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MF,) applied to a man, (S, A, L, Msb,) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~apN","text_ar":"خَبَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which casts doubt upon the assertion that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xab~N","text_ar":"خَبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally an inf. n., for were it so the masc. and fem. accord. to a general rule would be the same, as well as the sing. and pl.,] applied to a woman, (JK, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A great deceiver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very deceitful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, * S, A, L, Msb, * K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked and deceitful; a mischief-maker;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * A, * L, K, * TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, guileful, artful, crafty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cunning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mak~aArN","text_ar":"مَكَّارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 537, in explanation of the first and second.)       -A2-  Also the first of these words,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long, elevated tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habol","text_ar":"حَبْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", in some copies of the K erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jbl","text_ar":"جبل"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand, cleaving to the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":692},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract, between two rugged tracts, in which"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. in the former of which)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are truffles."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, K.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","S","A","L","Msb","K","MF"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}